fr.pixelprose.minimax4j

Class IA<M extends Move>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.pixelprose.minimax4j.IA<M>
  • Type Parameters:
    M - Implementation of the Move interface to use

    public abstract class IA<M extends Move>
extends Object
    Abstract class implementing minimax and derivated decision rules for two-person zero-sum games of perfect information. Extend this class to implement IA for several games, such as :
    • Chess
    • Reversi
    • Checkers
    • Go
    • Four-in-a-row
    • Tica Tac Toe
    • ...
    Author:
    antoine vianey

        public abstract List<M> getPossibleMoves()
        List every valid moves for the current player.

        "Improvement (of the alpha beta pruning) can be achieved without sacrificing accuracy, by using ordering heuristics to search parts of the tree that are likely to force alpha-beta cutoffs early."

        Returns:

      • evaluate

        public abstract double evaluate()
        Evaluate the state of the game for the current player after a move. The greatest the value is, the better the position of the current player is.
        Returns:
        The evaluation of the position for the current player

      • maxEvaluateValue

        public abstract double maxEvaluateValue()
        The absolute maximal value for the evaluate function. This value must not be equal to a possible return value of the evaluation function.
        Returns:
        The non inclusive maximal value

      • next

        public abstract void next()
        Change current turn to the next player. This method must not be used in conjunction with the makeMove() method. Use it to implement a pass functionality.
